Source: R/qldb_operations.R
qldb_describe_journal_s3_export.Rd

Returns information about a journal export job, including the ledger name, export ID, when it was created, current status, and its start and end time export parameters.

This action does not return any expired export jobs. For more information, see Export Job Expiration in the Amazon QLDB Developer Guide.

If the export job with the given ExportId doesn't exist, then throws ResourceNotFoundException.

If the ledger with the given Name doesn't exist, then throws ResourceNotFoundException.

qldb_describe_journal_s3_export(Name, ExportId)

Arguments

Name

[required] The name of the ledger.
ExportId

[required] The unique ID of the journal export job that you want to describe.

Request syntax

svc$describe_journal_s3_export(
  Name = "string",
  ExportId = "string"
)
